description: Request a list of field-level encryption profiles that have been created in CloudFront for this account.

nested_items.name: FieldLevelEncryptionProfileList
nested_items.description: Returns a list of the field-level encryption profiles that have been created in CloudFront for this account.

nested_items.name: NextMarker
nested_items.description: If there are more elements to be listed, this element is present and contains the value that you can use for the Marker request parameter to continue listing your profiles where you left off.

nested_items.name: MaxItems
nested_items.description: The maximum number of field-level encryption profiles you want in the response body.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of field-level encryption profiles.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: ID for the field-level encryption profile summary.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: The time when the field-level encryption profile summary was last updated.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: Name for the field-level encryption profile summary.

nested_items.name: EncryptionEntities
nested_items.description: A complex data type of encryption entities for the field-level encryption profile that include the public key ID, provider, and field patterns for specifying which fields to encrypt with this key.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: Number of field pattern items in a field-level encryption content type-profile mapping.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: An array of field patterns in a field-level encryption content type-profile mapping.

nested_items.name: PublicKeyId
nested_items.description: The public key associated with a set of field-level encryption patterns, to be used when encrypting the fields that match the patterns.

nested_items.name: ProviderId
nested_items.description: The provider associated with the public key being used for encryption. This value must also be provided with the private key for applications to be able to decrypt data.

nested_items.name: FieldPatterns
nested_items.description: Field patterns in a field-level encryption content type profile specify the fields that you want to be encrypted. You can provide the full field name, or any beginning characters followed by a wildcard (*). You can't overlap field patterns. For example, you can't have both ABC* and AB*. Note that field patterns are case-sensitive.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of field-level encryption field patterns.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: An array of the field-level encryption field patterns.

nested_items.name: Comment
nested_items.description: An optional comment for the field-level encryption profile summary. The comment cannot be longer than 128 characters.
